<task id="103" project="spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>BFF tests + publish + deploy; App Insights verification of lookup-first and text-fallback paths</title>
    <phase>G: Lookup-driven multi-index</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2-3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>102</dependencies>
    <blocks>104, 110</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, testing, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tests + deploy; no new code logic. Existing test suite + new tests added in 102 cover the behavior changes.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Sequential after 102 — verifies that task's deliverable.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add focused unit tests for the new resolver path (lookup-first + text-fallback) and `DataverseAllowedIndexesProvider` (cache + Dataverse-empty fallback). Run the full BFF test suite. Publish + deploy via `/bff-deploy` skill. Verify in App Insights that both code paths fire correctly when probed (one entity with lookup set, one with text-only).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    BFF developer comfortable with xUnit + Moq + the canonical deploy skill (`.claude/skills/bff-deploy/SKILL.md`).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Test suite green (existing + new tests for 102 behavior). BFF deployed to `spaarke-bff-dev`. App Insights shows resolver returning from BOTH paths during smoke probes (proves text-fallback is intact for migration soak; proves lookup-first works after seed in 101).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/</file>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/bff-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/phase-g/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md §12">Unit tests required: resolver lookup-first; resolver text-fallback (with WARNING log assertion); resolver returns null when both empty; provider cache hit/miss; provider Dataverse-empty fallback to appsettings.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 bullet 4">BFF publish-size verification — must be ≤ 60 MB compressed (current baseline ~45.65 MB).</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/skills/bff-deploy/SKILL.md">Deploy via the canonical `Deploy-BffApi.ps1`. Hash-verify + healthz are non-negotiable.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/skills/bff-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/phase-g/spec.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Add new unit tests under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/`: `SearchIndexNameResolverTests` (lookup-first, text-fallback w/ log assertion, both-null returns null, chain walks doc → parent → BU correctly under outer join). `DataverseAllowedIndexesProviderTests` (cache 100-rapid-calls assert one fetch, Dataverse-empty → appsettings fallback + warning log).</step>
    <step order="2">Run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` — all green.</step>
    <step order="3">Run `dotnet publish src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -c Release -o deploy/api-publish/` — verify compressed size ≤ 60 MB and report delta vs the baseline.</step>
    <step order="4">Invoke `/bff-deploy` skill (or run `scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` directly). Confirms hash-verify + healthz passes.</step>
    <step order="5">Smoke test: call `POST /api/ai/search` from `curl` (or the existing PCF) against (a) a Matter with `sprk_aisearchindexid` SET (expect lookup path), (b) a Matter with only `sprk_searchindexname` text set (expect text-fallback path + WARNING in App Insights). Confirm both return 200 OK with results.</step>
    <step order="6">App Insights query (per the skill): `traces | where timestamp > ago(15m) | where message has "PhaseG" | project timestamp, severityLevel, message`. Confirms at least one "TextFallback" warning + at least one normal lookup resolution within 15 min.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 103 🔲 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Bash">Run dotnet test + dotnet publish + scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">App Insights kusto query via az monitor command</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="tests">~6 new unit tests for resolver + provider</output>
    <output type="deploy">BFF deployed to spaarke-bff-dev; healthz=200; hash-verified</output>
    <output type="verification">App Insights traces showing both lookup-first and text-fallback paths firing</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` exits 0; new tests all pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish size compressed ≤ 60 MB; delta vs ~45.65 MB baseline reported in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`Deploy-BffApi.ps1` exits 0 with "All N critical files match" + healthz=200.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">App Insights kusto query shows at least one "PhaseG.TextFallback" WARNING and one normal lookup resolution within the 15-min window post-smoke.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
